  "text": "The Kafka network layer architecture consists of several interconnected components across the codebase:\n\n1. **NIO-based Selector** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/Selector.java): The core NIO selector implementation that handles non-blocking multi-connection network I/O. It works with NetworkSend and NetworkReceive to transmit size-delimited network requests and responses.\n\n2. **Byte Buffer Management** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/):\n   - NetworkReceive.java: Implements the Receive interface for managing incoming byte buffers\n   - NetworkSend.java: Implements the Send interface for managing outgoing byte buffers\n   - ByteBufferSend.java: A concrete Send implementation for ByteBuffer-based message transmission\n\n3. **KafkaChannel** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/KafkaChannel.java): Encapsulates communication with a single remote node, wrapping the low-level SocketChannel and coordinating with the Selector.\n\n4. **Server-side Architecture** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/network/):\n   - SocketServer.scala: The main server socket handler that manages the complete request/response flow:\n     - SocketServer class: Orchestrates the entire network layer, manages multiple listeners (data-plane, control-plane), and coordinates acceptors and processors\n     - DataPlaneAcceptor class: Handles incoming connections for data-plane listeners\n     - Acceptor abstract class: Base abstraction for accepting new socket connections and handing them off to Processor threads\n     - Processor class: Runs in dedicated threads, handles reads from sockets using the Selector and writes responses back\n   \n   - RequestChannel.scala: The handoff mechanism between Processor threads and request handler threads:\n     - RequestChannel class: Provides thread-safe queues for passing requests from Processors to handlers and responses back\n     - Request class: Encapsulates a network request with metadata and buffer management\n\n5. **Supporting Components**:\n   - Selectable.java: Interface defining the contract for socket-aware selectable objects\n   - Receive.java: Interface for receiving network data\n   - Send.java: Interface for sending network data\n   - TransportLayer.java: Abstraction for transport-level I/O operations\n   - ChannelBuilder.java: Factory interface for creating configured channels\n   - RequestChannelMetrics.java: Metrics collection for the RequestChannel\n\nThe flow proceeds as: Client connections → Acceptor threads (per listener) → Processor threads (with Selector) → RequestChannel → Handler threads → Response back through Processor threads → Selector → NetworkSend → Socket.\n"
}

